<item>
            <title>[LU-15999] t-f does not format journal with correct block size</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15999</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Without specifing &quot;-b block-size&quot; mke2fs creates journal_dev with &quot;Block size 1024&quot; on &quot;Journal size: 21M&quot; device and llmount.sh fails to create Lustre with external journal:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
   mke2fs: Filesystem has unexpected block size &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; trying
           to open journal device /dev/vdb
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;because the target device itself is created with default &quot;Block size: 4096&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
